value:
Moving your body can cure what ails
you... It's true! When I'm sad, I just go
for a run. The problem solves itself!

Retainers of Firene answer to the
queen. Growing up with Princess
Céline, I thought I would serve her...$k$pImagine my surprise when I got
a different assignment.

When your body gets worn out, you
need to rest your muscles so they
can recover. Why not give it a try?

I whipped up some new muscle balm.
I made it with Askran ingredients that
seemed good for sore muscles.

I'm planning to water the flowers...
It can be a good workout if the
watering can is full enough!

I ran all the way here to deliver
you a friendly message from
$Nf!

I'm full of energy! I hope I can make
good use of it!

Results like this come naturally after
putting in the work building muscles
like these.

Oh no! Time to visit the training
grounds, I guess.

Thank you! This will make me
stronger for sure.

I'm Etie, a royal knight of Firene and
Prince Alfred's retainer. Can you...
point me toward the training area?

I appreciate you giving me a place
to use my strength. So, let me say
thank you, $Nu.$k$pAs a token of my gratitude, I would
like to give you flowers from Firene,
but they don't grow here, so...$k$pI picked you some Askran flowers
instead. I found them growing around
the castle.$k$pMay they bring you strength and the
eternal affection you deserve.$k$pAnytime you need me, don't hesitate.
My bow and my strength are yours.$k$pEven if it's just to open a jar with
a stuck lid, I'll come running!
Scatter like petals!
I've got muscle to spare!
To strength!
Heavy draw!
Unbelievable...
I like to build a lean physique to emphasize agility. Tone before bulk.
Hey, watch it! That arm's sore from lifting.
You're always running around. I respect that.
That divine weapon of yours looks like it's got some heft. Mind if I give it a try?
Is it teatime? Let me go get my weighted cups.
The flowers of Askr are beautiful, too. I’m so glad.
I'd love for you to see the fields where I'm from. They're full of beautiful flowers... I'll show you—on a nice, long run.
Yeah.
Where to?
Let me at 'em.
